In re MORGAN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 12, 1903.) No. 150. Petition for Revision of Proceedings of the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Samuel Fleischman, for petitioners. Henry B. Johnson, for respondent.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Order affirmed, without intending to imply that the court considers the proposed amended specifications insufficient in form or substance.
